@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-teal-500 p-8 rounded-lg min-h-screen py-16">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-blue-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-white space-y-8 px-6 sm:px-10">
        <p class="text-xl">
            Your privacy is important to us. This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our Library Management System.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>
                We collect the following types of personal information when you interact with our system:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
                <li>Personal details such as your name, email address, and contact information.</li>
                <li>Library activity such as borrowed books, due dates, and reservation information.</li>
                <li>Browsing data such as your IP address and activity within the system.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>
                The information we collect is used for the following purposes:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
                <li>To provide and improve our library services and experience.</li>
                <li>To communicate with you regarding your library account, including book availability, due dates, and overdue notices.</li>
                <li>To analyze user behavior to enhance our system and services.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">How We Protect Your Information</h2>
            <p>
                We take the security of your personal information seriously. We implement a variety of technical and administrative measures to protect your data, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
                <li>Encryption of sensitive data during transmission and storage.</li>
                <li>Regular security audits and updates to our systems.</li>
                <li>Access controls to limit the exposure of your data to authorized personnel only.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>
                We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following situations:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
                <li>With service providers who assist in running the system, such as hosting or cloud services.</li>
                <li>If required by law or in response to legal requests, such as subpoenas or government investigations.</li>
                <li>To protect the rights, property, and safety of the library and its users.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
                You have the following rights regarding your personal data:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
                <li>The right to access the information we hold about you.</li>
                <li>The right to request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
                <li>The right to request the deletion of your personal information under certain conditions.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>
                We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, and the updated policy will be effective as soon as it is published.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800">Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                If you have any questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, please contact us:
            </p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:support@librarysystem.com" class="text-blue-900">support@librarysystem.com</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
